---
import CoursePageTemplate from '../../../layouts/CoursePageTemplate.astro';

const sections = [
  {
    title: "What is Python?",
    content: `
      <div class="bg-yellow-100 dark:bg-gray-800 text-yellow-900 dark:text-gray-100 rounded-lg p-4 mb-4">
        <p>Python is a high-level, interpreted programming language known for its simplicity and readability. Created by Guido van Rossum and first released in 1991, Python has become one of the most popular programming languages worldwide.</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 space-y-2">
          <li>Easy to learn and read</li>
          <li>Supports multiple programming paradigms</li>
          <li>Extensive standard library</li>
          <li>Large and active community</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Python's design philosophy emphasizes code readability with its notable use of significant whitespace and clean, simple syntax.</p>
      </div>
    `
  },
  {
    title: "Why Learn Python?",
    content: `
      <div class="bg-teal-100 dark:bg-gray-800 text-teal-900 dark:text-gray-100 rounded-lg p-4 mb-4">
        <p>Python is incredibly versatile and used across various domains:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 space-y-2">
          <li>Web Development (Django, Flask)</li>
          <li>Data Science and Machine Learning (NumPy, Pandas, TensorFlow)</li>
          <li>Artificial Intelligence and Deep Learning</li>
          <li>Automation and Scripting</li>
          <li>Game Development</li>
          <li>Scientific and Numeric Computing</li>
          <li>Desktop GUI Applications</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Its wide range of applications makes Python an excellent choice for beginners and professionals alike.</p>
      </div>
    `
  },
  {
    title: "Your First Python Program",
    content: `
      <p>Let's write your first Python program! In Python, printing is done using the <code>print()</code> function. It's a simple way to output text or values to the console.</p>
      <p>Here are some basic examples you can try in the code editor below:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 space-y-2">
        <li>Print a simple greeting</li>
        <li>Use variables to store and print information</li>
        <li>Perform basic calculations</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Don't be afraid to experiment and modify the code. Learning comes from trying things out!</p>
    `,
    code: `# Your First Python Program
# Print a simple greeting
print("Hello, World!")

# Using variables
name = "Python Learner"
print("Welcome,", name)

# Basic calculations
x = 10
y = 5
print("Addition:", x + y)
print("Multiplication:", x * y)

# Multiple data types
age = 25
height = 1.75
is_student = True

print("My age is", age)
print("My height is", height, "meters")
print("Am I a student?", is_student)`
  }
];
---

<CoursePageTemplate 
  title="Introduction to Python" 
  sections={sections}
/>
